WEBVTT

00:02.520 --> 00:06.040
I want you to be alive
after your entire family is dead.

00:06.120 --> 00:08.240
That is what will hurt you the most.

00:08.320 --> 00:11.080
TOMMY: <i>Michael is badly wounded.
John is dead.</i>

00:11.160 --> 00:13.400
<i>I sent a message to Aberama Gold.</i>

00:13.480 --> 00:15.320
-(GUNSHOT)
<i>.I need you back.</i>

00:15.400 --> 00:17.520
POLLY: <i>I'll help you
'cause Michael wants me to help you.</i>

00:17.600 --> 00:19.040
Starting now.

00:19.120 --> 00:20.480
ARTHUR: <i>The bullet's been written.</i>

00:20.560 --> 00:23.440
Me, as the oldest brother,
will put this bullet into his head.

00:23.520 --> 00:27.000
You said you'd bring
every man and woman out on strike.

00:27.080 --> 00:28.760
-Do you have a whistle?
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)

00:28.840 --> 00:30.680
JESSIE: <i>It's almost
as if you want trouble.</i>

00:37.040 --> 00:38.040
(CLANGING)

00:38.840 --> 00:40.320
(BIRD WINGS FLUTTER)

00:46.120 --> 00:47.600
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

00:53.280 --> 00:54.840
(ALL CLAMOURING)

01:04.920 --> 01:07.720
ARTHUR: All right,
first come, first served.

01:07.800 --> 01:09.960
Form an orderly line, all of you.

01:10.760 --> 01:12.360
All right. All right.

01:14.360 --> 01:15.760
Right!

01:15.880 --> 01:19.080
Have your contracts of employment
in your hand!

01:19.160 --> 01:21.200
Bring 'em in. Get in there.

01:21.960 --> 01:23.000
Get moving.

01:23.520 --> 01:24.680
On you go. Go on.

01:24.760 --> 01:26.240
Keep going. Keep going.

01:26.320 --> 01:27.800
You, where are you going?

01:27.880 --> 01:29.960
-Bradley. Foreman.
-All right.

01:30.040 --> 01:32.280
You go and see that man over there. Go.

01:34.440 --> 01:36.480
-What's your name?
-Bradley. I'm the foreman.

01:36.680 --> 01:38.520
-When did you last work here?
- 1922.

01:39.200 --> 01:40.760
How many have done
this type of work before?

01:40.840 --> 01:42.720
They're mostly farm hands
from down Worcester way.

01:42.800 --> 01:44.800
But I'll show 'em.
Hungry men learn fast.

01:44.920 --> 01:46.240
All right. On you go.

01:46.640 --> 01:49.240
STRIKER: Dirty scabs! Black legs!

01:50.960 --> 01:53.080
ARTHUR: What bastard threw that?

01:53.520 --> 01:55.320
Get him out here!

01:55.960 --> 01:58.040
Bring him out!

01:58.120 --> 01:59.120
It wasn't me!

01:59.840 --> 02:00.960
(GRUNTING)

02:05.040 --> 02:06.040
Arthur!

02:06.320 --> 02:07.320
Oi! Enough.

02:07.400 --> 02:09.120
Come on. Get him out. Get out!

02:09.200 --> 02:10.200
Get out!

02:10.320 --> 02:11.600
All right, ten more.

02:15.600 --> 02:16.600
Two more.

02:16.680 --> 02:18.000
-That's it.
-Ten.

02:18.080 --> 02:19.200
Close it up.

02:25.200 --> 02:27.480
Right. Ten bob a man.

02:28.040 --> 02:29.280
Two pound there for you.

02:29.360 --> 02:30.360
What about security?

02:30.440 --> 02:31.640
Yeah, well about that.

02:31.760 --> 02:34.520
By order of the city of Birmingham
police department,

02:34.600 --> 02:38.480
you and your ugly workforce
are now under the protection

02:39.760 --> 02:41.720
of the Peaky fucking Blinders.

02:42.880 --> 02:44.880
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

02:53.680 --> 02:56.120
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)
-(DOOR OPENS)

02:58.200 --> 03:00.400
-Mr Gray?
-Yeah, send him in.

03:00.880 --> 03:01.960
It's your mother.

03:02.640 --> 03:04.000
(SOFTLY) Oh, fuck.

03:13.760 --> 03:15.120
(DOOR SHUTS)

03:15.840 --> 03:17.640
I read about it in the paper.

03:20.080 --> 03:21.440
I have a right.

03:24.320 --> 03:26.120
I'm your mum as well.

03:32.040 --> 03:33.560
You want me to go away?

03:35.520 --> 03:36.520
Yes.

03:39.840 --> 03:41.320
I'll just leave these.

03:46.960 --> 03:48.440
They're from our orchard.

03:55.440 --> 03:56.640
You used to love these.

03:58.320 --> 04:00.240
I hope there are no worms in them.

04:07.360 --> 04:08.520
(EXHALES)

04:25.400 --> 04:26.480
Look,

04:27.520 --> 04:29.960
I just wanted to say
that you're welcome to come home.

04:31.840 --> 04:33.400
To get better at home.

04:34.200 --> 04:36.240
I know you got bored
in the village but...

04:38.320 --> 04:39.440
we love you.

04:40.760 --> 04:43.480
And your little brother
misses playing football with you.

04:45.440 --> 04:46.640
And your dad...

04:49.200 --> 04:51.000
passed on.

04:52.720 --> 04:55.000
He passed on peacefully in our bed.

04:58.160 --> 04:59.400
Oh, fuck.

05:05.560 --> 05:07.560
Now go home.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.120
I'm expecting Tommy.

05:09.520 --> 05:11.720
He's due here now.

05:13.600 --> 05:15.080
I'll go then.

05:17.000 --> 05:19.480
I'll not be in the same room
as that man.

05:34.320 --> 05:36.240
(DOOR OPENS AND SHUTS)

05:43.960 --> 05:45.600
(CAR APPROACHING)

06:04.720 --> 06:05.720
(DOOR SHUTS)

06:05.840 --> 06:08.080
Come on, Poll, Tommy's expecting us.

06:09.880 --> 06:11.480
Who's with us?

06:11.560 --> 06:13.600
Isiah and two Lee boys.

06:15.400 --> 06:18.560
Ada? How long since you've had a fuck?

06:19.800 --> 06:20.800
What?

06:21.440 --> 06:23.240
Been nearly two years with me.

06:24.280 --> 06:25.920
Over Christmas, I counted it up.

06:26.680 --> 06:29.960
So I've made a New Year's resolution
to change the situation.

06:30.120 --> 06:32.640
Oh. Anyone particular in mind?

06:33.680 --> 06:34.800
Not really.

06:36.080 --> 06:39.080
Just me and someone unsuitable.

06:41.400 --> 06:44.320
<i># From starry eyes colliding</i>

06:47.880 --> 06:51.920
<i># From Mars to someone crying</i>

06:53.840 --> 06:55.080
I'll sit in the front.

07:00.600 --> 07:03.840
<i># No matter what I'm hiding</i>

07:06.360 --> 07:08.400
<i># I get lost</i>

07:09.560 --> 07:12.520
<i># But I always come around</i>

07:12.960 --> 07:17.120
<i># Call when you're ready
'cause I'm ready to ride #</i>

07:18.280 --> 07:20.560
So this is just to make
business official.

07:20.640 --> 07:23.000
Your official return
to the company payroll.

07:23.080 --> 07:25.000
So no more talk
of New Year's resolutions

07:25.080 --> 07:26.640
or Tommy might change his mind.

07:26.720 --> 07:28.440
-What New Year's resolutions?
-(CHUCKLES)

07:28.800 --> 07:30.080
Never mind.

07:31.920 --> 07:34.240
I think Ada's trying to
tell me to behave myself.

07:34.320 --> 07:36.200
Yeah. Behave yourself.

07:37.560 --> 07:39.080
Behave myself or what?

07:40.760 --> 07:42.600
Behave myself or fucking what?

07:44.720 --> 07:46.560
Okay Polly, I'll tell you the truth.

07:47.080 --> 07:49.960
After your recent troubles,
Tommy asked me to keep an eye on you.

07:50.040 --> 07:51.120
Troubles?

07:52.640 --> 07:55.800
Whilst working for this company
I have killed a man,

07:56.280 --> 07:59.880
I have lost a man, I have found a son,
I have nearly lost a son,

07:59.960 --> 08:01.800
I have nearly lost my own life.

08:03.240 --> 08:06.320
Now I will accept my job back

08:06.400 --> 08:09.160
if the terms on offer are favourable.

08:11.920 --> 08:13.600
But I will not behave myself.

08:23.480 --> 08:24.680
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

08:25.040 --> 08:26.280
(DOOR OPENS)

08:27.440 --> 08:28.600
Sorry I'm late.

08:29.680 --> 08:31.000
(DOOR SHUTS)

08:38.520 --> 08:39.600
Where's Arthur?

08:42.040 --> 08:44.160
Do I look like his fucking mother?

08:53.480 --> 08:56.600
(DOOR OPENS AND SHUTS)

08:58.920 --> 09:00.000
No, Linda.

09:01.160 --> 09:02.160
Why are you here?

09:02.800 --> 09:04.440
You all right? Is Billy all right?

09:04.720 --> 09:06.720
Yes. Everything's fine.

09:06.800 --> 09:09.760
Well look, lovely to see you,
but I'm late for a meeting.

09:09.840 --> 09:11.000
They can wait.

09:18.800 --> 09:20.360
I've got something for you.

09:21.240 --> 09:23.640
Something for a loving husband
who's been working very hard

09:25.080 --> 09:27.760
and is under a great deal of pressure.

09:31.000 --> 09:34.200
Something to relieve his stress

09:34.840 --> 09:35.840
Oh.

09:42.680 --> 09:45.440
It's silk. From Japan.

09:46.640 --> 09:48.120
Feel.

09:52.960 --> 09:54.200
My hands are dirty.

09:54.320 --> 09:55.440
Good.

09:56.600 --> 09:57.640
Feel all of it.

09:58.360 --> 09:59.600
(ARTHUR EXHALES)

10:00.160 --> 10:01.240
Feel it properly.

10:01.760 --> 10:03.120
(BOTH SIGHING)

10:09.200 --> 10:12.880
You, uh, you want to do this here?

10:13.760 --> 10:16.280
Why not? I thought you were the boss.

10:17.560 --> 10:19.080
I am the fucking boss.

10:19.160 --> 10:21.280
So tell me what to do, boss.

10:23.560 --> 10:24.560
Come here.

10:25.680 --> 10:26.680
Right.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.880
Before we start
this extraordinary general meeting

10:29.960 --> 10:32.120
of the board
of the Shelby Company Limited,

10:32.760 --> 10:36.000
I'd like to note the absence
of the Deputy Vice President

10:36.160 --> 10:37.520
who has not yet arrived.

10:37.800 --> 10:39.440
We will continue without his presence.

10:40.120 --> 10:42.040
TOMMY: (CLEARS THROAT)
ltem number one.

10:42.600 --> 10:43.920
The reinstatement

10:45.600 --> 10:47.880
of the Shelby Company Limited
Company Treasurer.

10:48.440 --> 10:50.760
The board welcomes back
the former treasurer,

10:50.840 --> 10:53.560
with generously improved
terms and conditions.

10:53.880 --> 10:56.640
Due to the exceptionally
difficult circumstances

10:56.720 --> 10:58.360
the company now finds itself in.

10:58.600 --> 11:01.200
The proposed treasurer
will now check the terms and conditions

11:01.280 --> 11:02.760
to see if they are in order.

11:04.800 --> 11:06.080
Item number two.

11:06.640 --> 11:10.160
During the absence of the
Company Accountant, due to ill health,

11:10.320 --> 11:12.760
all responsibility for
the keeping of company accounts

11:12.840 --> 11:15.640
pass to the head of acquisitions.

11:17.680 --> 11:18.880
Item number three.

11:19.640 --> 11:22.400
The Company Treasurer,
having read the terms and condition,

11:22.480 --> 11:24.320
lodges a signed contract of employment

11:24.400 --> 11:27.520
agreeing to the terms and conditions
with the temporary head of accounts.

11:27.880 --> 11:31.920
All those in favour of the reinstatement
of Mrs Elizabeth Gray,

11:32.000 --> 11:34.440
to the position of Shelby Company
Limited Company Treasurer,

11:34.520 --> 11:36.240
please raise your hands.

11:37.280 --> 11:38.880
Why goodness, thank you.

11:38.960 --> 11:40.560
TOMMY: Any other business?

11:41.360 --> 11:45.160
Right. I declare this extraordinary
general meeting over.

11:46.560 --> 11:48.360
Now we can talk about the real business.

11:49.560 --> 11:50.880
But for that we need Arthur.

11:52.040 --> 11:53.600
Where the fuck is Arthur?

11:56.800 --> 11:57.880
(BOTH PANTING)

12:09.200 --> 12:10.600
(LINDA MOANING)

12:16.800 --> 12:19.320
-Mr Shelby...
-Fuck off.

12:19.520 --> 12:21.800
-They've broken into the paint shop.
-Oh, yeah?

12:21.880 --> 12:24.840
They're chucking paint around.
I think they mean to set light to it.

12:25.880 --> 12:29.440
Well, you deal with it, man.
I'm fucking busy!

12:33.240 --> 12:34.840
(BOTH GROANING)

12:54.480 --> 12:55.880
What was all that about?

13:12.320 --> 13:16.440
In this sinful place
there will be temptations.

13:17.080 --> 13:21.480
It's my responsibility as your wife
to help you resist those temptations.

13:23.160 --> 13:25.640
By putting myself between you...

13:30.920 --> 13:33.000
and the devil.

13:34.360 --> 13:36.400
In the words
of my sinful Catholic mother,

13:37.320 --> 13:40.280
"Keep his balls empty
and his belly full."

13:42.040 --> 13:43.800
God rest her soul.

13:45.600 --> 13:47.000
-(KNOCK ON DOOR)
-DEVLIN: Mr Shelby...

13:47.360 --> 13:50.400
You have to come
to the paint shop immediately. Please.

13:55.240 --> 13:56.560
I have to go.

13:57.760 --> 13:59.480
Won't be late.

14:01.320 --> 14:03.960
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)
-(DOOR OPENS)

14:04.560 --> 14:06.840
Sorry, ladies,
there's no smoking in here.

14:06.920 --> 14:08.360
Yes, love, we know.

14:11.040 --> 14:13.240
All right, he's an hour late.
Fuck him.

14:14.760 --> 14:18.440
This business directly affects Arthur,
but he's not here,

14:19.000 --> 14:20.320
so we'll take a vote without him.

14:20.760 --> 14:21.880
What business?

14:22.880 --> 14:25.320
Official business that wasn't
on your agenda, Ada.

14:25.920 --> 14:27.960
An informant told us

14:28.040 --> 14:31.960
that six years ago, Luca Changretta
came from New York to Birmingham

14:32.040 --> 14:33.960
to be best man at his cousin's wedding.

14:34.040 --> 14:36.600
POLLY: We found out that they used
Reid and Dunn on Broad gate

14:36.680 --> 14:37.920
for the photographs.

14:38.000 --> 14:39.720
The photographer kept the negatives.

14:39.800 --> 14:42.160
I persuaded him to give us copies.

14:42.640 --> 14:44.480
And to enlarge this one.

14:46.160 --> 14:49.240
That is Luca Changretta.

14:49.480 --> 14:51.840
TOMMY: I've seen his face,
so I could pick him out.

14:52.120 --> 14:54.800
Half the men in the photograph
are Changrettas,

14:54.880 --> 14:57.880
which means the chances are
they are the men who come to kill us.

14:58.400 --> 15:02.040
We need to get both these photographs
into pubs and on street corners.

15:02.120 --> 15:04.920
Then we put it about
that there's a reward for information.

15:08.200 --> 15:12.920
We also propose that we give a copy
of this photograph to Mr Aberama Gold.

15:13.880 --> 15:18.280
We need to forget the idea that it
has to be Arthur that pulls the trigger.

15:18.360 --> 15:19.800
Tradition will just fuck us up.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.080
We should wait for Arthur.

15:22.160 --> 15:23.920
Arthur's not here, Ada.

15:24.680 --> 15:28.040
We need Luca Changretta dead. That's it.

15:28.680 --> 15:29.760
Dropping the law of the bullet

15:29.840 --> 15:33.080
is part of the process of modernisation
that I was working on before I...

15:34.520 --> 15:35.840
Before I was executed.

15:36.640 --> 15:37.880
You weren't executed, Poll.

15:39.160 --> 15:40.400
What did you call me?

15:41.000 --> 15:43.080
TOMMY: Right. Let's take a vote.
I'll deal with Arthur.

15:43.160 --> 15:44.160
All those in favour

15:44.240 --> 15:47.840
of giving the photographs to Mr Gold,
raise your hand.

16:00.120 --> 16:02.160
Then it will be done.

16:02.240 --> 16:04.400
-Mum...
-Oh, "Mum" now, is it?

16:05.920 --> 16:07.600
I smelt perfume when I came in here.

16:07.680 --> 16:09.120
Yeah, it was the flowers.

16:10.760 --> 16:12.000
Right, that's it.

16:12.080 --> 16:13.680
Who came in here, Michael?

16:13.760 --> 16:17.320
The truth is, Polly,
the woman that raised him came in here.

16:17.400 --> 16:18.800
She has every right to come in here.

16:18.880 --> 16:21.040
She brought him fucking apples
and she left.

16:21.120 --> 16:23.680
TOMMY: We are in the middle
of a vendetta and Arthur is missing.

16:24.280 --> 16:25.560
We need to find him.

16:25.640 --> 16:27.840
Concentrate on what unites us.

16:28.800 --> 16:31.360
-TOMMY: This is all temporary.
-Yeah, temporary. Right.

16:40.280 --> 16:41.280
(DOOR SHUTS)

16:42.200 --> 16:44.760
<i># There's a devil inside of me</i>

16:45.760 --> 16:47.360
<i># He's holding on... #</i>

16:47.440 --> 16:48.520
MAN: Bastards!

16:48.600 --> 16:51.320
-(ALL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)
<i>.# And I don't know if he's staying</i>

16:51.400 --> 16:53.320
<i># Or for how long</i>

16:56.880 --> 16:59.480
<i># There's a devil inside of me.</i>

17:00.480 --> 17:02.840
<i># And he's holding on</i>

17:02.920 --> 17:08.120
<i># And I don't know if he's staying
or for how long... #</i>

17:09.280 --> 17:10.640
Party is it, eh?

17:11.000 --> 17:12.120
Is that what it is?

17:12.480 --> 17:14.800
What is this, a party, eh?

17:14.960 --> 17:17.200
Fuck off out of it! Get out!

17:17.720 --> 17:20.880
<i># And I'm sad to say
he's got me thinking</i>

17:20.960 --> 17:23.040
<i># About the bad parts of my life...</i>

17:23.120 --> 17:25.720
Okay, I wasn't gonna hit ya.

17:26.160 --> 17:27.880
But that wasn't fucking nice.

17:28.480 --> 17:32.960
<i># There's a devil inside of me
A monolith of doom</i>

17:33.040 --> 17:34.560
Oh, you...

17:36.800 --> 17:38.080
(MAN GROANING)

17:38.680 --> 17:40.400
MAN: Arthur... Mr Shelby, please.

17:40.480 --> 17:42.360
-Please.
-Don't fucking move.

17:43.640 --> 17:45.480
-Eh?
-Mr Shelby, please, please, please.

17:45.560 --> 17:47.360
Now get the fuck out!

17:49.480 --> 17:51.720
Fuck your fuckin' revolution!

17:51.800 --> 17:55.560
<i># I find I'm right back at the start #</i>

18:01.880 --> 18:03.880
I'm a fucking mess.

18:36.680 --> 18:37.680
Shh.

18:49.320 --> 18:51.760
(MEN SPEAKING ITALIAN, MUFFLED)

19:09.480 --> 19:11.480
(MAN SHOUTING IN ITALIAN)

19:30.200 --> 19:32.880
Where are you going?
Come here.

19:32.960 --> 19:34.600
Fucking hit man, are you?

19:34.760 --> 19:36.840
Eh? Is that what you are?

19:38.440 --> 19:39.640
Arthur Shelby, eh?

19:40.320 --> 19:41.880
Let's see who wanted you.

19:43.360 --> 19:44.640
What about...

19:44.800 --> 19:48.000
What about fucking John Shelby?

19:48.160 --> 19:49.160
Huh?

20:15.840 --> 20:17.640
John.

21:01.240 --> 21:02.240
Thank you.

21:03.720 --> 21:05.280
Send my guests in.

21:22.880 --> 21:24.520
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

21:50.040 --> 21:53.280
You wire Polo
and let him tell the family.

21:56.040 --> 21:57.560
He has four kids.

21:57.880 --> 21:58.880
(GRUNTS)

22:06.560 --> 22:09.200
Don't you two have
any other clothes to wear?

22:09.880 --> 22:10.880
Huh?

22:11.000 --> 22:13.080
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

22:19.120 --> 22:20.440
Look at me.

22:21.080 --> 22:22.080
Huh?

22:22.760 --> 22:25.160
I'm here as a lover of theatre.

22:28.280 --> 22:29.680
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

22:50.800 --> 22:52.720
They kill two of our men...

22:56.400 --> 22:58.240
You complain about your fucking belly.

23:01.960 --> 23:03.000
Luca.

23:04.560 --> 23:07.240
Luca. (SPEAKS ITALIAN)

23:08.120 --> 23:10.480
-With respect.
-"With respect"?

23:10.960 --> 23:12.600
You raised...

23:15.000 --> 23:16.240
"With respect"?

23:18.000 --> 23:19.600
Open your mouth.

23:20.440 --> 23:22.880
-Come on...
-Open your fucking mouth!

23:24.280 --> 23:26.040
You fucking dress like them.

23:26.640 --> 23:27.840
You eat like them.

23:28.480 --> 23:31.320
You don't fucking talk to me
about, "With respect".

23:33.840 --> 23:35.200
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

23:51.480 --> 23:52.720
Sit down.

24:02.240 --> 24:03.480
What do you have?

24:04.520 --> 24:06.040
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

24:14.360 --> 24:17.320
Arthur Shelby killed her son
in a boxing ring four years ago.

24:17.880 --> 24:19.680
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

24:33.160 --> 24:35.760
She would do that for us?

24:45.840 --> 24:47.040
Okay.

24:49.360 --> 24:50.600
Okay.

24:55.920 --> 24:58.760
-(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

25:15.680 --> 25:17.480
TOMMY: Anyone seen Arthur?

25:20.160 --> 25:21.680
Anyone seen Arthur? Eh?

25:22.240 --> 25:23.480
MAN: In your office, Tom.

25:30.440 --> 25:32.360
If you're not going to show up
for a family meeting,

25:32.440 --> 25:34.760
let someone know.
We thought you were dead.

25:34.840 --> 25:37.040
There's 15 fucking Italians out there.

25:37.280 --> 25:40.320
No there's not, there's 13.

25:41.240 --> 25:42.840
I just killed two of them.

25:43.800 --> 25:47.240
Ripped out their hearts
and burnt their bones to ash.

25:50.680 --> 25:52.800
I did it.

25:52.880 --> 25:54.440
Me.

25:54.520 --> 25:56.080
Your brother.

25:56.400 --> 25:59.800
Not fucking Aberama Gold
or his punch drunk son.

25:59.880 --> 26:01.120
But me.

26:03.120 --> 26:06.360
Even if you don't trust me no more.

26:06.440 --> 26:08.520
What the fuck are you talking about?
Arthur?

26:10.000 --> 26:12.040
I got cleaned up at Ada's.

26:12.880 --> 26:14.360
She told me.

26:14.800 --> 26:16.400
You took a vote in my absence.

26:16.480 --> 26:19.040
All right, calm down
and tell me about the men you killed.

26:19.120 --> 26:22.040
You put my job out for contract.

26:22.120 --> 26:23.200
Arthur...

26:24.440 --> 26:26.840
Yeah, well, I'm gonna make it
my fucking job anyway.

26:27.080 --> 26:29.040
Because this was all my fault.

26:29.760 --> 26:31.720
It was me that shot the old man.

26:31.840 --> 26:33.640
-Yeah, out of mercy.
-Aye.

26:34.360 --> 26:36.000
Now John's dead.

26:36.600 --> 26:40.000
He's dead because of me
and I'm gonna make it right.

26:41.040 --> 26:42.600
Arthur, wait.

26:43.760 --> 26:46.520
How did the men get in the factory?
I need to know.

26:50.360 --> 26:52.720
Through the back fucking door

26:53.400 --> 26:56.720
that was supposed to be
locked and bolted.

26:56.920 --> 27:00.720
Some bastard gave me up.
Somebody with keys.

27:02.160 --> 27:06.160
Yeah. Why don't you sit down
and work it out for yourself.

27:08.680 --> 27:10.680
Take a fucking vote.

27:27.440 --> 27:29.240
Who is this little bear?

27:29.320 --> 27:31.320
Yes. Eh?

27:35.200 --> 27:37.000
Are you all right?

27:40.880 --> 27:42.760
Daddy's home, isn't he?

27:43.720 --> 27:45.200
Yeah, I'm all right.

27:45.280 --> 27:47.080
Look, Daddy's home.

27:49.120 --> 27:50.160
How's Polly?

27:52.720 --> 27:54.160
Is she all right?

27:58.040 --> 27:59.840
Oh, go on, Linda.

28:01.240 --> 28:04.840
I mean, it was her idea,
wasn't it? Hmm?

28:05.080 --> 28:07.920
The Japanese silk? Hmm?

28:08.000 --> 28:09.640
I'll put him to bed.

28:20.160 --> 28:25.400
You kept me away from that
fucking meeting to stop me from voting.

28:25.480 --> 28:27.760
-Here we go.
-It was Polly's idea, wasn't it?

28:27.840 --> 28:29.480
-(BABY FUSSING)
-Eh?

28:30.960 --> 28:33.040
-You know what I am, don't ya?
-(SHUSHING)

28:33.480 --> 28:37.080
I'm a working man. Yeah.

28:38.800 --> 28:40.840
Fucking working man.

28:42.240 --> 28:43.600
Fucking...

28:44.160 --> 28:45.880
Who's lost his job.

28:49.800 --> 28:53.080
Is that what I am, Linda?
Is that what I am, eh?

28:56.240 --> 28:57.640
I don't want you dead.

28:57.960 --> 28:59.760
Polly doesn't want you dead.

29:00.120 --> 29:02.800
Let Mr Gold do the killing for money.

29:03.440 --> 29:05.120
It's the modern way, Arthur.

29:08.880 --> 29:10.480
Watch.

29:12.240 --> 29:14.560
Hmm? Hmm?

29:22.000 --> 29:23.360
What are you doing?

29:25.440 --> 29:28.640
Now fire it into the fireplace.

29:29.160 --> 29:30.400
Please.

29:33.760 --> 29:35.800
-All right.
-Fire it.

29:38.000 --> 29:39.520
Get rid of it.

29:45.200 --> 29:46.960
Then we'll go to bed.

29:47.880 --> 29:49.520
We'll do anything you like.

29:50.560 --> 29:52.920
Just fire the gun, Arthur.

29:53.800 --> 29:55.280
Fire it.

29:55.440 --> 29:56.800
Ah!

29:57.320 --> 29:59.320
You go tell Polly...

30:01.680 --> 30:05.480
there are rules between a man and woman.

30:07.200 --> 30:08.800
There are rules.

30:14.640 --> 30:16.560
That I have to do this.

30:19.520 --> 30:21.320
I have to do it.

30:23.960 --> 30:26.320
John wants me to do it, Linda.

30:30.160 --> 30:31.480
My brother...

30:34.080 --> 30:35.800
And I'm gonna do it!

30:47.840 --> 30:49.320
(DOOR SHUTS)

31:23.640 --> 31:25.640
Was it fear or was it hatred?

31:27.240 --> 31:28.960
Was what fear or hatred?

31:30.040 --> 31:31.240
Isiah...

31:38.440 --> 31:41.440
You had a one way ticket to Glasgow
in your pocket.

31:45.480 --> 31:47.840
Your wife and kids left three days ago.

31:49.200 --> 31:52.240
Now, I'm gonna ask you again.

31:55.160 --> 31:57.200
Was it fear of the Italians

31:57.840 --> 31:59.080
or hatred of us

31:59.840 --> 32:03.240
that made you unlock the door
and give up my brother?

32:03.680 --> 32:05.720
I didn't unlock any door.

32:10.240 --> 32:12.040
Here, have a drink.

32:12.920 --> 32:14.680
You're gonna need it.

32:18.200 --> 32:21.840
Thirty five Drumcree Street,
Park head, Glasgow...

32:21.920 --> 32:24.800
Please, please, please, please...

32:25.440 --> 32:28.680
We have allegiances
with Catholic gangs in that city.

32:28.760 --> 32:32.160
Your family are safe
only at my discretion.

32:33.000 --> 32:39.640
Now, explain to me why you were
catching the midnight train to Glasgow.

32:41.200 --> 32:42.720
You mean you don't know?

32:44.440 --> 32:47.680
I run a factory
full of black leg non-union lab our.

32:48.240 --> 32:51.360
I live in a street
full of men laid off or on strike.

32:53.080 --> 32:55.280
Look at the photograph, Mr Devlin,
and tell me who are the men

32:55.360 --> 32:57.120
-that contacted you.
-No.

32:57.200 --> 32:59.480
-No, you listen to me.
-(CLEARS THROAT)

32:59.560 --> 33:03.720
I get spat at, windows smashed,
petrol on the curtains.

33:03.800 --> 33:07.000
But for fear of you
I clock in every fucking morning.

33:07.520 --> 33:10.960
And today, two men are shot
and burnt on my shift.

33:11.040 --> 33:13.920
And you ask me why I'm getting on
the midnight train to Glasgow.

33:23.640 --> 33:25.480
Who else has the keys to that door?

33:26.320 --> 33:28.760
They hang on a hook inside my office.

33:30.040 --> 33:32.080
Today I left the office unlocked.

33:32.160 --> 33:34.040
-Why?
-Because I forgot.

33:34.600 --> 33:35.800
Because I left in a hurry.

33:35.880 --> 33:38.480
Because there were men
trying to set fire to the factory.

33:40.720 --> 33:43.880
Mr Shelby, may I tell you something?

33:45.680 --> 33:47.520
You have a lot of enemies.

33:48.880 --> 33:52.040
Communists. Italians.

33:55.920 --> 33:58.040
Before the factory came out on strike,

33:58.120 --> 34:03.360
I heard word that two Italians attended
a communist party meeting in Stechford.

34:04.560 --> 34:06.240
They hardly spoke English.

34:07.280 --> 34:10.760
Now, if they got a party man
into the factory,

34:10.840 --> 34:13.280
it might have been him
that unlocked the door for them.

34:17.440 --> 34:21.520
Mr Shelby, my train leaves at 12:00.

34:21.600 --> 34:25.040
It's just gone 11 :00.
I can still make it.

34:27.160 --> 34:30.440
Please. For my kids.

34:37.640 --> 34:39.040
I need you here.

34:39.120 --> 34:42.520
Isiah, get three of our men
with police badges

34:42.600 --> 34:44.240
to watch Mr Devlin's house.

34:44.320 --> 34:46.040
DEVLIN: Mr Shelby, please...

34:48.880 --> 34:51.640
Our friends in Glasgow
will take care of your family.

34:53.560 --> 34:55.240
For the curtains.

34:57.040 --> 35:00.600
Before you, I was
an ordinary working man.

35:00.960 --> 35:03.200
Yeah, and now you're one of us.

35:24.240 --> 35:26.920
<i>(BYE, BYE, BLACKBIRD</i> PLAYING)

35:35.080 --> 35:39.840
<i># Blackbird, blackbird
Singing the blues all day</i>

35:40.280 --> 35:43.680
<i># Right outside of my door... #</i>

36:03.160 --> 36:04.840
(MUSIC STOPS)

36:07.400 --> 36:09.760
-Who is it?
-Tommy Shelby.

36:14.800 --> 36:17.120
-Is this union business?
-Yes.

36:17.200 --> 36:19.640
So conduct it in the proper place
at the proper time.

36:20.280 --> 36:22.000
I've come to make an improved offer.

36:34.960 --> 36:36.360
I heard music.

36:37.360 --> 36:39.120
What's your improved offer?

36:39.880 --> 36:42.200
-Do I not get a drink?
-No.

36:49.960 --> 36:52.320
Have you ever seen any of the men
in this photograph before?

36:53.480 --> 36:54.560
What?

36:59.560 --> 37:02.520
You're a member
of the Stechford Communist party.

37:03.040 --> 37:05.800
I'm told two Italian men
attended a meeting recently.

37:06.320 --> 37:09.200
Can you see either of the men
in this picture?

37:13.760 --> 37:15.960
As the Small Heath coordinator

37:16.160 --> 37:18.240
of the Organisation
for the Maintenance of Supplies

37:18.320 --> 37:20.480
I have also been sworn in
as a Special...

37:20.560 --> 37:22.160
(SCOFFS)

37:22.960 --> 37:26.560
We have reason to believe
that outside agitators from overseas

37:26.640 --> 37:29.720
are attempting to foment trouble
in our factories

37:29.800 --> 37:33.600
in advance of a General Strike
which could take place at any moment.

37:34.080 --> 37:35.880
This is a matter of national security.

37:37.160 --> 37:38.600
May I look at your badge?

37:40.240 --> 37:41.920
Yes.

37:43.920 --> 37:45.320
(CLEARS THROAT)

37:52.680 --> 37:54.280
What would you like to drink, Constable?

37:54.360 --> 37:56.560
Whisky.
And, actually, it's Sergeant.

37:57.480 --> 37:59.120
I only have beer. Times are hard.

38:00.160 --> 38:02.600
How long has it been since you've had
a bottle of M&B bitter?

38:03.840 --> 38:05.000
Help yourself.

38:09.040 --> 38:10.280
Have a seat.

38:17.560 --> 38:21.400
You know, when this business began,
I did some research on you.

38:22.200 --> 38:24.880
It turns out I know someone
who used to know you very well.

38:26.040 --> 38:27.280
KittyJurossi.

38:31.880 --> 38:34.840
You were in love with Kitty's sister.
Greta Jurossi. Before the war.

38:34.920 --> 38:36.600
Do you remember Greta Jurossi?

38:38.800 --> 38:40.720
Her parents were Italian.

38:41.240 --> 38:44.920
They didn't approve of a Watery Lane
Gypsy, but you won them over.

38:45.040 --> 38:47.960
With your charm. Sweetness.

38:50.720 --> 38:54.440
Very, very thorough research.

38:54.920 --> 38:58.360
Greta died at the age of 19.
Of consumption.

39:00.400 --> 39:04.240
And Kitty said you were at her bedside
for three months.

39:04.320 --> 39:06.160
Every day, holding her hand.

39:07.640 --> 39:09.760
And after she died you went away to war.

39:12.000 --> 39:14.680
Kitty said that the sweet boy who left
never came back.

39:15.080 --> 39:16.600
No one came back.

39:18.160 --> 39:19.640
Here's the funniest thing.

39:21.120 --> 39:23.600
She said in those days
you believed in things.

39:23.880 --> 39:26.320
In justice. Fairness.

39:27.360 --> 39:29.560
Once you saw a man beating his horse
and you fought him.

39:29.640 --> 39:31.480
He was twice your size but you beat him.

39:31.560 --> 39:33.320
And then you beat him with his own whip.

39:35.440 --> 39:37.680
Kitty always liked to tell tall tales.

39:38.720 --> 39:40.280
She's a party member now.

39:41.640 --> 39:43.680
She swears
before you enlisted in the army

39:43.760 --> 39:46.040
you joined the Communist party yourself.

39:47.960 --> 39:49.280
(CLEARS THROAT)

39:50.160 --> 39:51.560
Is that true?

39:58.040 --> 40:00.000
(MUSIC RESUMES)

40:02.040 --> 40:06.480
You know, when I was at the door,
I saw you through the curtains.

40:07.800 --> 40:09.360
You were dancing alone.

40:13.040 --> 40:15.240
I've also done my research.

40:21.080 --> 40:24.080
Your sweetheart was at Passchendaele.

40:25.320 --> 40:28.720
When he came back,
he was listed among the shell shocked.

40:29.920 --> 40:31.880
Blew his own fucking brains out.

40:40.920 --> 40:42.520
I don't know any men in the photo.

40:47.120 --> 40:48.320
You haven't looked.

40:50.000 --> 40:53.800
This afternoon two men came into
my factory and tried to kill my brother.

40:54.240 --> 40:57.120
I believe a Stechford Communist party
member let him in.

40:57.760 --> 41:01.200
I was wondering if you might be able
to help me in my investigations.

41:07.440 --> 41:11.200
Kitty said next time I see you,
before we start fighting,

41:11.880 --> 41:14.240
I should send you her love
from the good old days

41:15.240 --> 41:16.640
and give you this.

41:18.960 --> 41:23.000
Greta Jurossi and Tommy Shelby
in Blackpool.

41:33.040 --> 41:34.760
Do you recognise the boy
in the photograph?

41:58.720 --> 42:00.080
I'll leave that here.

42:04.480 --> 42:06.360
Apologies for interrupting your dance.

42:11.680 --> 42:12.960
(DOOR OPENS)

42:15.080 --> 42:16.160
(DOOR CLOSES)

42:47.120 --> 42:50.480
<i># I wish</i>

42:52.280 --> 42:57.280
<i># I wait</i>

42:58.840 --> 43:02.560
<i># But it's all in vain</i>

43:03.720 --> 43:11.000
<i># I wish I was a maid again</i>

43:11.920 --> 43:15.240
<i># But a maid again</i>

43:16.120 --> 43:21.160
<i># I never can be</i>

43:22.640 --> 43:28.880
<i># Till apples grow... #</i>

43:29.200 --> 43:32.800
Arthur... I need you to listen to me.

43:35.120 --> 43:37.120
I need you to listen to me, Arthur...

43:41.160 --> 43:42.840
The world is changing.

43:46.040 --> 43:47.680
Listen to me, Arthur.

43:49.880 --> 43:52.720
And listen to the sweet voice
of Jesus...

44:45.400 --> 44:49.120
<i># I wish...#</i>

44:49.840 --> 44:51.840
(GUNSHOT)

44:53.320 --> 44:55.400
-Finn?
-It came from Arthur's house.

44:58.200 --> 44:59.440
Arthur.

45:02.000 --> 45:03.200
Arthur.

45:03.360 --> 45:04.600
Where is he?

45:06.640 --> 45:07.800
Arthur.

45:08.920 --> 45:10.200
He fired the bullet.

45:13.800 --> 45:15.360
Linda...

45:16.560 --> 45:19.040
Said it's the modern way, Tom...

45:22.600 --> 45:24.080
It's the modern way.

45:24.520 --> 45:26.320
Yeah. Yeah.

45:27.240 --> 45:28.640
Yeah, it's all right.

45:30.880 --> 45:32.280
It's all right, brother.

45:38.880 --> 45:39.920
You did well.

45:40.000 --> 45:41.760
God spoke to him, not me.

46:07.200 --> 46:08.480
POLLY: What are you doing here?

46:08.720 --> 46:10.720
On Mondays, I do the inventory.

46:11.000 --> 46:12.760
Make sure nobody's dipping their hand.

46:13.920 --> 46:16.440
Well, it's my job now.

46:17.920 --> 46:19.040
I'm back.

46:19.160 --> 46:21.720
And there's gonna be nobody
dipping their hand with me here,

46:22.040 --> 46:24.160
not unless they want it cut off.

46:35.400 --> 46:37.520
I said to Arthur
while I'm stuck in this fucking place

46:37.600 --> 46:39.280
I want something to keep my mind busy.

46:39.600 --> 46:41.160
What? You're going to take bets?

46:41.280 --> 46:44.680
I have always been able to do addition
and subtraction without pen and paper.

46:45.160 --> 46:46.680
But I'll need a telephone.

46:47.440 --> 46:50.680
Apparently we have special clients
who take bets by telephone.

46:50.760 --> 46:51.840
Linda?

46:54.040 --> 46:55.400
This is a betting shop.

46:56.040 --> 46:57.080
Look.

46:57.640 --> 46:59.840
Arthur said yes. Tommy said yes.

46:59.920 --> 47:02.440
But did God say yes?
Gambling is a sin, Linda.

47:02.760 --> 47:04.520
It's not me that's doing the gambling.

47:05.280 --> 47:06.680
I'm just taking the bets.

47:16.800 --> 47:19.880
The rule is that door should always
remain locked until 9:00 A.M.

47:22.480 --> 47:25.800
Right. Boy. Boy, where are you going?

47:26.520 --> 47:29.360
Well, Arthur's not coming in today.
He's taking the day off. So...

47:29.800 --> 47:31.120
So what?

47:31.200 --> 47:33.960
So today, Tommy said that I'm in charge.

47:34.320 --> 47:35.840
Sorry, you're in charge?

47:37.680 --> 47:38.960
Yeah. That's what he said.

47:43.680 --> 47:45.360
All right, sweetheart.

47:49.160 --> 47:50.400
Ladies?

47:50.520 --> 47:53.680
Let's give our boss a first day

47:54.400 --> 47:55.760
that he'll never forget.

48:04.440 --> 48:05.520
(DOOR OPENS)

48:05.960 --> 48:07.960
Sending Finn to the shop was a mistake.

48:08.040 --> 48:09.760
They've already found out
he's a virgin

48:09.840 --> 48:12.080
and they're arranging a girl for him,
this afternoon.

48:13.240 --> 48:14.360
I thought Linda was there.

48:14.880 --> 48:18.000
-She is. She loved the idea.
-(SCOFFS)

48:18.080 --> 48:20.200
I know. She even swears now.

48:20.400 --> 48:21.440
"Fuck".

48:21.720 --> 48:23.080
Sounds funny coming from her.

48:23.160 --> 48:25.320
Polly says in the end
we all turn into our mother.

48:26.000 --> 48:28.000
Well, keep an eye on her.

48:28.120 --> 48:29.120
Hmm.

48:30.320 --> 48:32.360
The whore watching the Madonna.

48:33.400 --> 48:35.120
Does Finn know what they have planned?

48:35.200 --> 48:36.560
No.

48:36.640 --> 48:38.000
Do they have someone?

48:38.440 --> 48:41.360
Yes. A girl I used to work with.

48:43.840 --> 48:45.720
-Is she nice?
-No.

48:46.080 --> 48:47.240
She's from Aston.

48:47.720 --> 48:49.440
They're paying her out of petty cash.

48:49.640 --> 48:51.000
Right, well, call 'em

48:51.960 --> 48:53.520
and tell them to pay extra

48:54.560 --> 48:55.760
and get someone nice.

48:56.560 --> 48:58.360
Nice women don't do that sort of thing.

48:58.840 --> 49:01.040
Yes, they do. What about you?

49:03.840 --> 49:06.480
I mean in the past. Come on.

49:07.120 --> 49:08.440
Where are we going?

49:08.520 --> 49:10.800
Somewhere I've not been in a long time.

49:20.440 --> 49:22.040
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

49:29.720 --> 49:31.600
Are we expecting somebody?

49:35.040 --> 49:36.880
Tommy, I'm fucking freezing here.

49:40.080 --> 49:41.680
We used to come here.

49:44.000 --> 49:46.520
She'd wait for hours for me,

49:46.600 --> 49:48.160
when I couldn't make it.

49:49.760 --> 49:51.360
And I'd wait for her

49:52.280 --> 49:54.360
if her family kept her in.

49:56.000 --> 49:57.720
Who?

49:59.320 --> 50:00.680
Some girl.

50:01.640 --> 50:03.600
Some girl before France.

50:09.280 --> 50:10.800
I've not been back here since.

50:17.400 --> 50:18.960
But I wanted to come here with you.

50:31.680 --> 50:33.680
Are you kissing her or me?

50:36.320 --> 50:38.120
You.

51:23.680 --> 51:25.520
I want Shelby Company Limited

51:25.600 --> 51:28.800
to increase non-taxable
charitable contributions

51:28.880 --> 51:31.760
to local charities
by twenty-five percent

51:32.040 --> 51:33.080
as of now.

51:34.480 --> 51:36.080
And I'm gonna build

51:36.160 --> 51:38.480
two new institutes
for destitute children.

51:38.560 --> 51:41.040
One in Saltley, one in Digbeth.

51:41.720 --> 51:43.600
I've already identified the buildings.

51:43.680 --> 51:45.240
Two former workhouses.

51:47.160 --> 51:50.440
I want you to be
in charge of the project.

51:52.040 --> 51:53.280
All right, come on, let's go.

51:53.760 --> 51:54.960
Why?

52:02.920 --> 52:05.840
Because I promised someone
I'd change the world.

52:09.600 --> 52:12.680
You do realise, Tommy,
we're all going fucking mad here.

52:13.720 --> 52:15.360
Yeah, I know.

52:16.080 --> 52:17.280
Come on.

52:22.720 --> 52:23.960
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

52:29.520 --> 52:32.000
Finn? Come here.

52:36.360 --> 52:39.000
-How was your day?
-Yeah, it was okay.

52:40.600 --> 52:42.040
Good man. Well done.

52:42.600 --> 52:44.000
No trouble?

52:44.080 --> 52:46.120
No. No trouble.

52:48.280 --> 52:49.720
And she looked after you?

52:55.320 --> 52:57.240
I don't want it like that
ever again, Tom.

52:58.320 --> 52:59.840
Not when they don't even want to do it,

53:00.400 --> 53:01.680
except for the money.

53:02.200 --> 53:03.760
Everything's for the money, Finn.

53:04.120 --> 53:06.560
Yeah, I know. But...

53:08.640 --> 53:10.200
She said, "Be a man."

53:12.240 --> 53:14.640
And were you a man?

53:14.720 --> 53:15.760
Yeah.

53:17.320 --> 53:20.960
But then I apologised to her.
Because she looked so tired.

53:25.280 --> 53:26.880
Sit down, Finn.

53:29.320 --> 53:30.480
(CLEARS THROAT)

53:30.840 --> 53:32.680
Right, listen to me, Finn.

53:33.320 --> 53:34.440
She was right.

53:35.440 --> 53:37.800
You need to be a fucking man.

53:37.880 --> 53:39.560
People get tired.

53:39.640 --> 53:42.640
Working in a fucking factory
gets you tired.

53:43.120 --> 53:45.320
I don't go round apologising.
Do I?

53:45.640 --> 53:46.680
No.

53:46.760 --> 53:49.080
There's an empty space here
to be filled.

53:49.600 --> 53:50.840
Do you understand?

53:51.480 --> 53:52.960
-Yeah.
-So...

53:53.720 --> 53:55.160
Be a fucking man.

53:57.640 --> 53:59.320
Okay, Tom.

54:13.040 --> 54:14.840
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

54:17.720 --> 54:19.640
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

54:43.080 --> 54:44.880
-Champagne, please.
-Of course.

54:46.760 --> 54:47.760
Madam...

54:48.640 --> 54:51.880
Women alone are not allowed at the bar.

54:52.360 --> 54:53.800
Will someone be joining you?

54:54.840 --> 54:56.160
What do you think?

55:30.160 --> 55:31.280
(MUSIC ENDS)

55:31.360 --> 55:33.240
(APPLAUSE)

55:40.280 --> 55:42.040
(BAND PLAYING JAZZ MUSIC)

55:42.120 --> 55:43.760
This is public enough, no?

55:44.920 --> 55:46.320
Yes.

55:49.680 --> 55:50.680
So?

55:52.600 --> 55:54.840
The boy in the hospital
is out of bounds.

55:54.920 --> 55:57.280
And I will ask you
to spare Finn and Arthur.

56:00.360 --> 56:02.320
In return for what?

56:07.560 --> 56:08.840
Tommy Shelby.

56:14.800 --> 56:17.560
And, uh, why should I trust you?

56:19.760 --> 56:21.520
Because you know our history.

56:24.080 --> 56:25.800
You know what happened between us.

56:28.640 --> 56:31.000
You are an unlikely Cassius.

56:32.920 --> 56:33.920
LUCA: Mmm...

56:38.640 --> 56:41.360
You know, my mother...

56:43.240 --> 56:45.000
My mother knew your mother.

56:47.560 --> 56:49.640
She taught her how to read.

56:51.400 --> 56:54.520
Did she tell you
that John and Arthur spared her life?

56:54.600 --> 56:56.120
When Tommy wanted her dead.

56:56.360 --> 56:57.800
Yeah.

56:58.920 --> 57:02.080
And now she's given me
the information about you people.

57:03.720 --> 57:06.240
So Tommy Shelby was right.

57:09.040 --> 57:11.720
His, uh, ruthlessness

57:13.520 --> 57:15.320
was justified.

57:16.720 --> 57:19.600
You should have killed her
when you had the chance.

57:21.800 --> 57:23.800
John was a good boy.

57:27.360 --> 57:28.760
Arthur tries.

57:30.680 --> 57:32.480
Tommy's different.

57:33.920 --> 57:37.040
You take Tommy.
Spare the rest.

57:42.200 --> 57:43.680
You know,

57:44.880 --> 57:47.400
my mother used to say this about you.

57:49.200 --> 57:51.600
She said,
"That Polly Gray,

57:52.960 --> 57:56.040
"that child would never
let go of a grievance."

58:00.440 --> 58:02.360
And she loves to dance.

58:06.840 --> 58:08.480
What do you say, huh?

58:09.840 --> 58:11.720
You want to dance?

58:17.520 --> 58:19.360
I don't dance any more.

58:21.360 --> 58:23.200
Well, that's a shame.

58:30.680 --> 58:32.280
'Cause you're dancing with me.

58:39.400 --> 58:41.400
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

58:55.520 --> 58:59.560
<i># On a gathering storm comes
a tall handsome man</i>

58:59.640 --> 59:04.240
<i># In a dusty black coat
with a red right hand #</i>

59:04.264 --> 59:09.264
http://hiqve.com/
